Entrypoint directory: 
    All scripts under this directory and sub-directories should be run from this directory. All the script-paths are relative to this directory.
    To use these scripts in any other bash script do a 'cd' to this directory first in a sub-shell, e.g., (cd root_dir && ./xyz.sh)

Entry script:
    ./.setup: call this to change to full Gnome session
    ./.revert: call this to revert back to XRDP session default

Installers:
    /xrdp_gnome_session_setup.sh: complete installation script

Uninstallers:
    ./.revert: revert back to XRDP session default
    ./gcm_uninstaller.sh: uninstalls gcm only

Commands:
    setXrdpGnuSession: 
        - use this command to get full GNU session experience.
        - symbolic link is created in /usr/local/bin/mycommands
        Usage: setXrdpGnuSession
    revert2XrdpSession:
        - use this command to revert back to XRDP session experience.
        - symbolic link is created in /usr/local/bin/mycommands
        Usage: revert2XrdpSession